<br>
The only real difference in my mind between people who prostitute themselves for sex and people who prostitutes themselves as retail managers or customer service reps or actuaries is that one is illegal and the others aren't.  So, why is it illegal?  Simply put, selling sex offends the morality of a sizable group of people.  However, many of daily dangers faced by prostitutes would be eliminated if it were legalized and controlled.<br>
<br>
I don't think that the government should be legislating morality in regards to victimless crimes (no personal or property damage).  Much of the violence inherent in the current system of prostitution would be eliminated if it were taken off the streets and out of the control of pimps.  <br>
<br>
