Drugs:  Personally, can't stand them anymore.  I quit smoking two years ago, I drink rarely.  I tried a number of illicit drugs between the ages of 18 and 21, but didn't into any of them.  Now, caffeine and food are my drugs. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
During my late teens/early twenties when I was in school, I lived with both people who smoked pot a lot and people who drank a lot.  In my experience, I would pick the potheads any day of the week.  They were more pleasant, didn't get into fights, never vomited except when ill, rarely called in sick to work after a night of heavy use, kept their jobs, and paid their bills on time.<br>
<br>
Tobacco and alcohol kill many more people than pot does.  The only real reason pot has &quot;victims&quot; is because of the governmental persecution of its users, and the fact that violence is an inherent part of the black market.  Should people be stoned on the job or driving cars? No.  But that is the current status with alcohol, and pot is a hell of a lot less dangerous.<br>
